WEBVTT

00:00.610 --> 00:01.191
Well, good morning.

00:02.573 --> 00:03.534
My name is Levi Gardner.

00:03.554 --> 00:05.637
I'm one of the pastors here at Perdido Bay Methodist Church.

00:05.677 --> 00:07.539
And I joined Scott of welcoming you today.

00:07.619 --> 00:11.645
It is a joy to worship Christ alongside of you today.

00:11.685 --> 00:19.114
As I was reminded, it is a day like this that we are thankful for the mercies of Jesus that are new every morning, even on a time change day.

00:19.134 --> 00:19.455
Amen.

00:20.556 --> 00:24.882
Yeah, when my oven looked at me and said it was 320, I said, well, glory be to God in the highest.

00:27.202 --> 00:29.025
I do love the mornings, but eight o'clock I'm done.

00:29.065 --> 00:30.467
But hey, catch me in the morning, I'm good to go.

00:31.528 --> 00:34.413
As Pastor Scott said, it is a great day to be here.

00:34.433 --> 00:37.297
And if you are a guest with us, I'm glad that you're here today.

00:37.377 --> 00:46.290
That might seem weird for most pastors to say, but it's an opportunity for you to see the heart of this community face.

00:46.330 --> 00:56.786
And then we're gonna be talking about in just a few minutes is the reality that this church has had the generational impact that it has because of the willingness of the whole.

00:56.962 --> 01:03.489
to take on their part of giving and investing in the kingdom of heaven through their time, their talents, their gifts, their service, and their winners.

01:03.509 --> 01:17.646
This church is never dependent on one or two people to do everything, but it has been a commitment of the whole of all of those who make this their church family to be the hands and feet of Christ, helping our community to know the message of Jesus.

01:17.686 --> 01:25.074
And so I'm thankful today as we look at the promise that we hear in scripture that Jesus Christ is the same yesterday

01:25.218 --> 01:30.546
today and this morning we're focusing on the fact that Jesus Christ is the same forever.

01:31.047 --> 01:39.160
And so I want us to turn at to Psalm 22 for our first scripture and then our second scripture will come to us from Hebrews chapter 13.

01:39.200 --> 01:41.023
Let us listen for the word of the Lord.

01:42.385 --> 01:46.472
The Psalmist writes, I will give praise and the great assembly because of you.

01:47.433 --> 01:50.218
I will fulfill my vows before those who fear you.

01:50.899 --> 01:53.042
The humble will eat and be satisfied.

01:53.570 --> 01:55.552
Those who seek the Lord will praise him.

01:55.612 --> 01:57.835
May your hearts live forever.

01:57.895 --> 02:01.480
All the ends of the earth will remember and turn to the Lord.

02:02.321 --> 02:04.804
All the families of the nations will bow down before you.

02:05.525 --> 02:07.347
For kingship belongs to the Lord.

02:07.968 --> 02:09.289
He rules the nations.

02:10.070 --> 02:12.553
All who prosper on earth will eat and bow down.

02:12.613 --> 02:18.560
All those who go down to the dust will kneel before him, even the one who cannot preserve his life.

02:19.381 --> 02:20.803
Their descendants will serve him.

02:20.823 --> 02:23.186
The next generation will be told about the Lord.

02:23.714 --> 02:27.358
They will come and declare His righteousness to a people yet to be born.

02:27.999 --> 02:29.560
They will declare what He has done.

02:29.620 --> 02:39.631
Hebrews 13, Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today, and forever.

02:39.671 --> 02:45.558
Therefore, through Him, let us continually offer up to God a sacrifice of praise.

02:46.318 --> 02:49.141
That is the fruit of lips that confess His name.

02:49.982 --> 02:53.426
Don't neglect to do what is good and to share for God is pleased

02:53.634 --> 02:54.876
with such sacrifices.

02:55.557 --> 02:57.860
This is the word of God for the people of God.

02:58.441 --> 02:59.402
Thanks be to God.

03:00.103 --> 03:07.934
Heavenly Father, may the words in my mouth and the meditation in my heart be pure and acceptable in your sight, O Lord, our rock and our redeemer.

03:08.735 --> 03:09.096
Amen.

03:11.179 --> 03:16.306
I love how the psalmist opens this passage calling our eyes

03:16.482 --> 03:20.047
Heaven, we're bringing the grand scheme of time to the forefront.

03:20.508 --> 03:25.015
I will give praise in the great assembly because of you.

03:25.035 --> 03:29.281
He's calling our eyes to the throne of God.

03:29.321 --> 03:40.498
He's saying, in the presence of any who watch, in the presence of all those who joined alongside of me, I come before you, God, to offer my unfettered praise.

03:41.058 --> 03:52.676
And this is what I believe God has been working in our congregation over these last several months as a yearning, a hunger, simply for the presence of God in our life.

03:53.357 --> 04:02.831
As we sang earlier, the Holy Spirit would dwell with us that we wouldn't be more aware of how God is moving and acting in the midst of our church and in the midst of our lives.

04:02.851 --> 04:04.914
And this is what the psalmist is declaring.

04:05.282 --> 04:11.330
The God you are active, God you are powerful, God you are good and so, I will praise you.

04:11.350 --> 04:23.386
And as I come before you God, I declare that I'm making a vow to love you, to serve you, to worship you, to honor you and all that I do.

04:23.426 --> 04:35.122
And I give thanks that last Sunday night our women's ministry gathered in here to pray, to simply be in the presence of God, to adore Him, to bring their confessions before Him, to lift their thanks, giving to Him, and to ask

04:35.202 --> 04:36.985
God to move in their life.

04:37.025 --> 04:41.572
And we know that God is moving in the lives of all of those who pray.

04:41.592 --> 04:51.887
And this is why we're having an emphasis on having people before the service that are available to pray with you because we know that when we pray, God moves.

04:51.907 --> 04:54.672
When we pray, God listens.

04:55.493 --> 04:59.158
When we pray, we are changed.

05:01.863 --> 05:04.146
God invites us to His scripture.

05:05.058 --> 05:20.663
to see ourselves in the midst of the great assembly, to recognize that your voice, your vow, is valuable to the king of heaven and earth, that he yearns to hear your love for him.

05:20.744 --> 05:27.154
He yearns to see your devotion to him because he has created you into his very image.

05:27.586 --> 05:35.336
And he has given you gifts, and he has given you a purpose, and he wants you to see your role in bringing the kingdom of God to bear.

05:35.376 --> 05:48.253
It's not simply the responsibility of the person on the left, of the right, but it is the call, the privilege, the honor of all of those who call themselves followers of the risen Lord.

05:48.894 --> 05:51.717
I will give praise in the great assembly.

05:52.518 --> 05:55.282
And I give thanks last week for the testimony of

05:55.394 --> 06:17.198
Micah and Katie Skinner, as they talked about how they have experienced that, as they have gotten more involved in the community of faith here, how in the midst of their serving, in the midst of their being in small groups, that they have experienced this truth, that they have found themselves in the midst of this assembly here, and they have encountered the presence of God anew, and they would testify that their family has been changed.

06:17.818 --> 06:24.786
Their lives have been changed, because when we encounter the presence of the living God, we

06:24.898 --> 06:27.261
leave changed and transformed.

06:27.842 --> 06:34.211
And that's why we gather each and every week because we know that God has something for us today.

06:34.832 --> 06:50.775
As we encounter His Word, as we encounter His presence, and so we continually seek for the Lord to bless us today, but also to cast our eyes to tomorrow because we know He is the God that was, the God that is, and the God that is to come.

06:51.617 --> 06:52.658
And so we worship

06:53.186 --> 06:56.551
for Thanksgiving, but we also worship with expectation.

06:57.453 --> 07:16.021
But for us to live into this truth that Jesus Christ is the same forever, it requires us to have faithfulness, to have trust in the present, but also to have generosity to, for that generosity to compound so that the next generation can take the mantle of faith.

07:16.041 --> 07:21.810
Continue moving forward with what we are doing today because we know that the church of tomorrow is present today.

07:22.274 --> 07:30.105
that these young people that were worshiping out front, yes, they are the church of the future, but they're also the church today, but if we don't invest in them today, there will be no church of tomorrow, amen?

07:31.807 --> 07:51.314
This is why the book of Deuteronomy says, teach your children the word of God in coming and going, because we know that as the faith is shared, as the faith is lived, our children see that the same Jesus that saved us is the same Jesus that is saving them in the same Jesus that will save their children and their children's children.

07:52.962 --> 07:57.369
the prayers that we pray today, the gifts that we give today.

07:57.810 --> 08:09.267
We may not see the evidence or the work of those gifts and those prayers, yet we do these things with the trust that God alone can bring the harvest and that God will bring the harvest into His time.

08:09.327 --> 08:21.266
And we pray that we can see the fruit of our harvest, but we know there will be some things that we plant today that God will fulfill generations from now, but yet we serve and we give and we trust because we know that God is faithful.

08:22.082 --> 08:24.946
He's faithful because we've experienced it in our life.

08:25.788 --> 08:30.274
He's faithful because we talk to our ancestors and we hear how he was faithful to them.

08:30.294 --> 08:35.081
And we know he is faithful because God is the God who keeps his promise.

08:36.103 --> 08:41.571
And so we gather and we rejoice for the God who is and but also the God who will be.

08:41.631 --> 08:51.666
We make this statement on a hope, on a pattern of God's goodness and on the guarantee that he makes.

08:52.162 --> 09:01.619
that He is the Alpha and the Omega, the beginning and the end, the first and the last, and the because He lives, we too shall live.

09:01.899 --> 09:03.101
That's not a guest church.

09:04.043 --> 09:04.945
That's not a speculation.

09:04.985 --> 09:05.866
That's a guarantee.

09:05.926 --> 09:11.556
Only God can guarantee the future.

09:12.779 --> 09:14.381
And so we claim His Word.

09:15.003 --> 09:16.946
We claim His promise.

09:17.314 --> 09:40.049
and we stand firmly upon it for where we are going as a church, where we are going as followers of Jesus, because we know this church that the gospel of Jesus Christ, the mission of our church to lead our community to life in Jesus Christ, that the need for the world to know the gospel, that the truth of the gospel is never going to change.

09:40.229 --> 09:40.550
Amen?

09:44.316 --> 09:45.778
Many products.

09:46.274 --> 09:55.669
have to think about what consumer sentiment or consumer desires are going to be in 10, 15, 20 years they're designing sodas or designing clothes or designing handbags.

09:55.990 --> 09:58.754
We don't have to worry about the need for the gospel.

10:00.056 --> 10:01.018
It's going to be there.

10:01.038 --> 10:06.226
We have a product that stands from age to age.

10:06.754 --> 10:09.378
We have the truth that will save people in China.

10:09.398 --> 10:11.540
We have the truth that will save people in Africa.

10:11.560 --> 10:18.670
We have truth that will save people in Pensacola, Florida because Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today and forever.

10:19.972 --> 10:21.254
We don't have to modify it.

10:21.474 --> 10:22.595
We don't have to dress it up.

10:22.615 --> 10:33.490
We simply have to stand on the Word of God to stand on the foundation that has been entrusted to us for this day and to pass it on to the church that is to come.

10:34.498 --> 10:36.882
But in this moment, we are the stewards of today.

10:36.922 --> 10:40.568
The pearl of great price has been entrusted to us.

10:41.630 --> 10:44.936
And so Jesus says, Church, how are you trusting me today?

10:44.976 --> 10:51.407
How are you serving me today so that there might be the bright future of the church tomorrow?

10:51.427 --> 10:55.634
Because Jesus has much ahead for us.

10:56.226 --> 11:00.993
He has much ahead for us as followers of him individually, but also for this community of faith.

11:01.053 --> 11:01.814
But here's the good news.

11:02.115 --> 11:05.820
If Jesus Christ came back in glory this afternoon, he still has a future.

11:05.880 --> 11:12.870
We are tied up in his living, in his reign, in his kingdom.

11:13.631 --> 11:17.998
And because he has made the promise we walk faithfully into tomorrow.

11:19.400 --> 11:22.724
And so we look and we listen for where God is leading us.

11:22.764 --> 11:23.826
Many of you know we have

11:23.906 --> 11:28.931
a multi-year strategic plan and ministry that we're looking to grow new ministries, new opportunities.

11:29.571 --> 11:33.575
And one of those is a beginning of a robust men's ministry.

11:34.076 --> 11:50.471
And we're living into that plan beginning this, in just a couple of months, we're gonna have our first men's fellowship dinner on April the 10th, because we know that there is a hunger in our church for men to gather in the name of the Lord, to be in relationship with one another, to be in friendship with one another, to pray for one another.

11:50.511 --> 11:53.714
So we're saying, Lord, help this to come to be.

11:54.338 --> 12:00.665
And this is something that we discerned years ago when we are seeing the fruit of the seeds that were sown in that coming to fruition.

12:00.685 --> 12:05.129
So we're praying for God to move amongst the men of our church in a mighty way.

12:05.169 --> 12:09.914
But that's just one of many things that we know God has on the horizon for us.

12:10.775 --> 12:19.564
But we can only live into those possibilities if we are faithful, if we are generous, if we are trusting in God to do what God says He will do.

12:20.705 --> 12:21.266
I love

12:21.506 --> 12:35.339
how pastor Scott shared so poignantly last week that we can't be so consumed with what we did yesterday, that we forget we still have a responsibility tomorrow, that we need to give thanks for what God is doing today.

12:36.280 --> 12:41.625
But we can't be so lost in today that we forget that Jesus has much ahead for us.

12:42.666 --> 12:50.674
So God invites us in our hearts to consider how His faithfulness in the past, His faithfulness in the present,

12:51.106 --> 12:53.669
That these are gifts that God has graciously given to us.

12:54.650 --> 12:59.896
Gifts that God has revealed to us that we might entrust him with all of our tomorrows.

13:02.039 --> 13:04.822
God gives us our daily bread.

13:06.364 --> 13:09.888
God calls us to be trusting in what he gives us today.

13:10.769 --> 13:18.898
But I also love the story where God gives a dream to Joseph that he might store up grain for a time when there will be a shortage of grain.

13:19.586 --> 13:32.238
We see God promises daily bread, but God also gives us wisdom to steward our gifts for the foundation of the future, to know that there will be a people to come, that we are building the church for them now.

13:33.400 --> 13:38.605
And so God gives us the call to be faithful today, but also to trust Him for tomorrow.

13:39.986 --> 13:48.114
God reminds us of the promise in Deuteronomy that He is a God who is faithful to a thousand generations.

13:49.378 --> 13:53.545
This is how we can say with certainty that Jesus Christ is the same forever.

13:54.486 --> 14:00.476
Because this is the God who says, I am who I am and I will be who I will be.

14:00.536 --> 14:03.761
Our God is not shifting sand.

14:04.963 --> 14:07.167
Our God is not going to change.

14:07.247 --> 14:13.277
Our God is immovable, unshakeable, all knowing, all powerful, all faithful.

14:14.318 --> 14:16.562
And He invites us to trust in that.

14:17.762 --> 14:28.559
So many times we put our trust in things that will let us down, that will change, that will falter, but Jesus promises His unchanging faithfulness.

14:29.821 --> 14:36.432
And what are the ways that we can experience that faithfulness, experience that trust is through our generosity?

14:37.193 --> 14:43.022
I'm so thankful that from a very young age, I was taught to trust God with those first fruits, right?

14:43.262 --> 14:45.586
I had a $2 allowance, big money, kids.

14:47.746 --> 14:54.214
20 cents went into the tide jar for the very first allowance I got.

14:55.536 --> 15:00.602
Because from a very young age, I learned that we don't have to live off of everything that we get.

15:00.642 --> 15:07.370
That if we trust God with the first fruits, there will always be enough and some left over.

15:07.851 --> 15:09.032
That's the beauty of the baskets.

15:09.893 --> 15:12.917
They took the fish and the loaves and there was enough and some left over.

15:13.297 --> 15:14.719
I don't get it, but it's God math.

15:14.759 --> 15:15.700
It's like the redemption store.

15:15.760 --> 15:17.202
I don't get it, but it works.

15:21.506 --> 15:27.614
We are entrusted with much so that we can be faithful with what we are given.

15:28.495 --> 15:31.940
We freely receive so that we can joyfully give.

15:33.421 --> 15:37.967
We are not to grasp anything tightly except the hem of the garment of our Savior.

15:39.309 --> 15:45.677
Everything else we are called to hold loosely, to say, Lord, even my life I offer to you.

15:46.859 --> 15:47.900
This is not my own.

15:47.960 --> 15:49.202
It is yours, O Lord.

15:50.274 --> 15:56.661
Everything that I have, everything that I am, is and will always be yours.

15:57.802 --> 15:59.064
So God, I trust you.

15:59.945 --> 16:02.027
God, use me as you will.

16:03.028 --> 16:05.010
Use my finances as you will.

16:05.050 --> 16:07.232
Use my family as you will.

16:07.393 --> 16:08.814
Use my home as you will.

16:08.874 --> 16:11.017
Use my car as you will for Lord.

16:11.117 --> 16:12.018
It isn't mine.

16:13.619 --> 16:16.082
It is a gift from you to be used for your glory.

16:17.698 --> 16:26.071
When we think about this, it changes our perspective because it allows us to see the faithfulness of God day in and day out.

16:27.073 --> 16:29.536
And this is why I love the wisdom of Hebrews 13, 16.

16:29.677 --> 16:33.082
It says, don't neglect to do what is good and to share.

16:33.122 --> 16:37.268
For God is pleased with such sacrifices.

16:38.390 --> 16:40.553
What's one of the earliest lessons we teach our kids?

16:41.595 --> 16:41.976
Share.

16:42.036 --> 16:46.162
But as adults, we say, no, that's mine.

16:48.706 --> 16:50.669
If our kids said that, we would be appalled.

16:53.513 --> 16:59.001
God is honored and pleased with such sacrifices that are shared.

17:00.383 --> 17:04.570
But God desires not that we give these with tight fists and gridded teeth.

17:06.052 --> 17:09.817
God desires for us to share and to give with thanksgiving.

17:10.959 --> 17:12.501
Giving is joyful.

17:13.082 --> 17:15.666
Giving is to be celebratory.

17:16.098 --> 17:19.643
Giving is not to be something that is a burden upon your back.

17:20.705 --> 17:28.316
It is meant to be freeing for us to recognize the source of all that we have and all that we are and all that we will be.

17:29.338 --> 17:34.565
Because as we give joyfully, we begin to experience the mighty hand of God.

17:35.567 --> 17:45.682
Everything that we do is a congregation only happens because of your generosity, because of your faithfulness to show up, to serve.

17:46.370 --> 18:00.469
Nothing else is making the ministry of this church happen, but the people of this church week in and week out day in and day out, sometimes minute in and minute out being willing to give and to serve so that God can show up in mighty and powerful ways.

18:01.751 --> 18:03.814
This has been the story of our church.

18:04.555 --> 18:06.698
This is the story of our church.

18:07.179 --> 18:15.570
And this will continue to be the story of our church, that this is our opportunity to invest mightily in what God is doing today.

18:15.938 --> 18:19.822
so that we can trust the seas that we are sowing now for the church of tomorrow.

18:20.623 --> 18:22.846
Because we know that Jesus is already going ahead of us.

18:23.607 --> 18:26.870
We know what Jesus is going to be doing, who Jesus is and what he promises.

18:27.731 --> 18:30.014
And so we don't have to worry about what we are giving to.

18:30.034 --> 18:41.787
We are giving to the Lord of all creation, the one who is seated at the right hand of the Father, the one who again will come and glory to judge the living and the dead and in whom his kingdom will have no end.

18:43.148 --> 18:44.530
Nations will rise and fall.

18:45.922 --> 18:47.544
Houses will be built and torn down.

18:49.207 --> 18:51.930
Even our lives are like vapors in the wind.

18:53.633 --> 18:56.617
But the Lord stands forever.

18:57.979 --> 19:00.662
And because He lives, we too shall live.

19:01.724 --> 19:04.628
I love the great Him because He lives.

19:05.369 --> 19:06.530
This hymn has been on my hearts.

19:06.570 --> 19:10.275
I consider the fact that Jesus Christ is the same forever.

19:10.315 --> 19:15.122
And if you are familiar with the hymn, this is the chorus because

19:15.394 --> 19:16.175
He lives.

19:17.317 --> 19:18.378
I can face tomorrow.

19:19.420 --> 19:21.143
Some of us just need that word today, man.

19:22.665 --> 19:25.870
Because he lives all fear is gone.

19:26.250 --> 19:28.834
I don't care what the news tells you, church, that's the truth right there.

19:28.914 --> 19:36.165
Because he lives all fear is gone because I know he holds the future.

19:37.226 --> 19:37.948
Oh, what good news?

19:39.770 --> 19:44.978
He holds the future and life is worth the living.

19:45.250 --> 19:49.535
just because He lives.

19:52.078 --> 20:06.635
Because Jesus lives and will live and forevermore will be, we are invited to experience the joy of that abundant life, of what He gives us that we can entrust all things to Him.

20:06.675 --> 20:12.242
And we're gonna hear a brief testimony from Kathy Jeffcoat, who has been

20:12.610 --> 20:21.043
a part of starting this church many years ago and who's been a faithful member and someone who's invited more people to be a part of this church than I can count.

20:21.363 --> 20:23.366
And she has experienced God's faithfulness.

20:23.386 --> 20:30.838
I want you to hear how she shared a word from 25 years ago and then how she is reflecting upon God's faithfulness today.

20:34.564 --> 20:41.394
When the opportunity came for my family to move to this church, I saw this as a great opportunity

20:41.666 --> 20:49.697
for young families and young people in this community to become part of something really special.

20:49.977 --> 21:02.995
And that's one of the reasons I left Pleasant Grove to come to Prudido Bay because I knew that their God had a lot of people in this community that he needed to become a part of this church.

21:03.675 --> 21:05.959
And this church is like a family to me.

21:06.499 --> 21:08.562
When I come in this church, it's like coming home.

21:09.570 --> 21:16.478
Good morning, I'm Kathy Jeffco, and for 35 years, my family has been attending and been members of this church.

21:17.419 --> 21:23.526
Some of you out there weren't even born 35 years ago, and I didn't know you were gonna be here today, but God did.

21:24.387 --> 21:38.002
So for so many years, God has given me the opportunity to share the good news of Jesus Christ to people in my community, just by inviting them to services or offering for them to come to Bible study or Sunday school with me.

21:38.690 --> 21:40.372
You have that opportunity today.

21:40.432 --> 21:45.878
We continue to be able to offer that to everyone in our community and to our friends.

21:46.359 --> 21:48.501
That's what the stewardship campaign is all about.

21:49.162 --> 21:54.228
Allowing us to give just a small portion back to Jesus who gives so generously to us.

21:54.808 --> 21:57.111
Always, this church is like an anchor.

21:57.632 --> 22:00.115
It reminds us to look up and not down.

22:00.195 --> 22:04.460
It reminds us that Jesus is with us no matter what happens in our lives.

22:04.680 --> 22:06.642
Over the years, our lives have changed.

22:06.946 --> 22:11.573
And a lot of times people ask us, are you going to move?

22:11.633 --> 22:13.416
Are you going to downsize?

22:13.916 --> 22:16.280
And the first thing I tell everybody is, I can't move.

22:16.721 --> 22:17.562
My church is here.

22:18.063 --> 22:20.086
And I can't go anywhere and leave my church.

22:20.466 --> 22:28.338
We have so many saints that are cheering us on, so many people that help build what we are able to enjoy today.

22:28.738 --> 22:38.751
Someday you may be sitting here where I am, and you're gonna have the opportunity 20 or 30 years from now to say to the people out there, I didn't know you'd be here today, but God did.

22:39.432 --> 22:45.380
May God continue to bless everyone that walks through the doors of this church today, tomorrow, and forever.

22:45.861 --> 22:46.161
Amen.

22:50.066 --> 22:55.794
The closing of Psalm 22, here again, these words, their descendants will serve him

22:56.354 --> 22:58.658
The next generation will be told about the Lord.

22:59.600 --> 23:04.227
They will come and declare His righteousness to a people yet to be born.

23:04.287 --> 23:06.932
They will declare what He has done.

23:06.972 --> 23:13.924
This truth remains the same church, that those who come after us will serve the same Jesus.

23:14.785 --> 23:22.258
The next generation yearns to be told about the Lord, that they are eager to come and to declare His righteousness

23:22.754 --> 23:34.790
And so if people yet unborn, they too, one day, will declare what the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, the God who sent Jesus Christ to dwell among us, the God who died on Calvary for our sins has done.

23:34.830 --> 23:37.654
But this is our moment.

23:38.335 --> 23:46.386
This is our time to say yes to what God is doing, but to say, Lord, we trust you for what you will bring tomorrow.

23:46.786 --> 23:48.488
We can't see over the horizon.

23:48.528 --> 23:56.037
We don't know what's around the corner, but we know who is already standing there paving the way, guaranteeing the future.

23:56.918 --> 24:13.739
And so may we take the bold step today of continuing to trust God with our time, to trust God with our lives, to trust God with our giving, knowing that we do this with the sure and certain hope that Jesus Christ is the same yesterday.

24:14.720 --> 24:16.562
Jesus Christ is the same today.

24:16.866 --> 24:19.811
And Jesus Christ will be the same forever.

24:19.851 --> 24:21.202
Amen.

